The paper deals with first-order logic over words and monoids, which falls under the category of logic (cs.LO). It also discusses circuit classes and their uniformity, which could be classified under computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of numerical predicates and the study of definability of languages suggest a connection to formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). The paper also mentions cyclic groups and their properties, which could be related to discrete structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the separation of different circuit classes, which could be classified under information theory (cs.IT).
